**Class Definition and Header File**  
We begin by defining a class named `UndergraduateStudent` which will encapsulate all the required properties of a university undergraduate student. This class will include private member variables to store the student's full name, unique ID, and GPA. Public member functions will allow for the initialization, modification, and retrieval of these properties.

```cpp
#ifndef UNDERGRADUATESTUDENT_H
#define UNDERGRADUATESTUDENT_H

#include <string>

class UndergraduateStudent {
private:
    std::string fullName;
    std::string uniqueID;
    double gpa;

public:
    // Constructor
    UndergraduateStudent(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double initialGPA);

    // Setter methods
    void setFullName(const std::string& name);
    void setUniqueID(const std::string& id);
    void setGPA(double newGPA);

    // Getter methods
    std::string getFullName() const;
    std::string getUniqueID() const;
    double getGPA() const;

    // Method to update GPA based on new course grades
    void updateGPA(double newGradePoints, int totalCreditHours);
};
#endif // UNDERGRADUATESTUDENT_H
```

*highlighted section*  
**Implementation File**  
Next, we implement the methods defined in the header file. The constructor initializes the student's name, ID, and GPA. The `updateGPA` method is designed to adjust the GPA based on new grade points and credit hours, simulating the process of updating a student's academic record.

```cpp
#include "UndergraduateStudent.h"

UndergraduateStudent::UndergraduateStudent(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double initialGPA)
    : fullName(name), uniqueID(id), gpa(initialGPA) {}

void UndergraduateStudent::setFullName(const std::string& name) {
    fullName = name;
}

void UndergraduateStudent::setUniqueID(const std::string& id) {
    uniqueID = id;
}

void UndergraduateStudent::setGPA(double newGPA) {
    gpa = newGPA;
}

std::string UndergraduateStudent::getFullName() const {
    return fullName;
}

std::string UndergraduateStudent::getUniqueID() const {
    return uniqueID;
}

double UndergraduateStudent::getGPA() const {
    return gpa;
}
